BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:mTew6y8S4vWplSZDQkMlv
SUMMARY:Boren Banner Series: Camille Trautman
DTSTAMP:20260401T021327Z
DTSTART:20260411T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Every photograph is a reminder that the act of framing is never
	 neutral. In Camille Trautman’s first solo museum exhibition in their home
	town\, the Seattle-born Duwamish artist uses photography and video to chal
	lenge colonial narratives and counter Indigenous erasure. The exhibition p
	resents selections from their ongoing series The North American LCD—spectr
	al self-portraits staged in varied natural landscapes. Rooted in Trautman’
	s process of coming out as transgender\, the images show the artist’s body
	 partially obscured by large LCD screens. The series examines how both lan
	dscape photography and digital media can shape or distort cultural identit
	y\, often by promoting or denying visibility.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.
	com/events/#/details/boren-banner-series-camille-trautman/16813305/2026-04
	-11T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/boren-banner-series-camil
	le-trautman/16813305/2026-04-11T00
LOCATION:Frye Art Museum\, 704 Terry Ave\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT6H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:_mquEY1weO9mrlS80m0qR
SUMMARY:LS 301: Front of House Mixing
DTSTAMP:20260401T021327Z
DTSTART:20260411T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:The final course of VERA’s Live Sound series\, this three-hour 
	workshop includes practice mixing a live band in a low pressure environmen
	t\, starting with the basics of soundcheck and ending with a full blown mi
	x. Subject matter will include: Setting up a front of house mix on an M32 
	board\, preamps\, EQ settings\, mixing styles for different genres\, sound
	 pressure levels\, outboard gear techniques and lots of critical listening
	 to ensure that show attendees\, artists\, and staff have a great experien
	ce at the show.\n\nStudents must complete both LS 201: Small PA Mixing and
	 LS 202: Mixing for Monitors before you can take this class.\n\nThis class
	 is a prerequisite for shadowing and ultimately becoming the Lead Sound En
	gineer at Vera Project shows. Each Live Sound class unlocks new audio engi
	neering volunteer shifts at Vera and eventually paid opportunities in and 
